# BACKEND (.NET)

Source: [`docs/CONSTITUTION.md`](docs/CONSTITUTION.md), [`docs/TECHNICAL.md`](docs/TECHNICAL.md). Consult `core.mdc` first. Tests → `backend-testing.mdc`.

**Do not load architecture/CQRS/EF skills** — those topics are fully covered in Constitution and Tech §2–6.

## Naming and documentation

From Constitution VI — also summarized in `core.mdc`:

- No `/// <summary>` (or other XML doc) on types or members.
- No abbreviations in identifiers (`ApplicationDatabaseContext`, `userIdentifier`, `cancellationToken`; not `*Db*`, not `ct`).
- No `Trading` prefix on types or files.
- Each project has `AssemblyReference.cs`; register handlers, validators, and EF configurations via `AssemblyReference.Assembly`.

## Stack

- **.NET 10**, nullable on, warnings as errors where project enables it
- **MediatR** — commands/queries; pipeline order in Constitution II.5 / Tech §4
- **FluentValidation** — every command; failures never reach handler
- **EF Core** — Infrastructure only; read queries `AsNoTracking` by default (Tech §6)

## Layer layout

See Tech §2–3. Match existing `AddApplication` / `AddInfrastructure` extension patterns in the codebase when wiring DI.

## Application (CQRS)

Sample commands: `RegisterUser`, `LoginUser`, `LogoutUser` (Tech §4).

- Queries return **Contracts DTOs** — never domain entities on the read side
- **Concurrency:** `row_version` + bounded retry at handler boundary (Constitution III.9)

## DON'TS

- ❌ No domain rules in Api endpoints — MediatR handlers only
- ❌ No `Task.Result` / `.Wait()` — async throughout
- ❌ No raw SQL strings — EF LINQ or parameterized APIs
- ❌ No reading `Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable` in handlers — `IOptions<T>` at startup
- ❌ No catching `Exception` without log + appropriate rethrow/result
